The paper deals with the problem of aligning images, which is a core problem in computer vision. The use of deep learning techniques such as spatial transformer networks and auto-encoders suggests that the paper is likely to be in the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on unsupervised learning and the use of penalised reconstruction also suggest that the paper could be in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The application of the proposed method to co-segmentation, super-resolution, image edit propagation, structure-from-motion, and 3D reconstruction suggests that the paper could also be in the multimedia (cs.MM) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
